The paper deals with sampling techniques for data mining problems, which are typically studied in the computer science subfields of data structures (cs.DS), databases (cs.DB), and data mining (cs.DM). The paper also discusses applications in graph mining, which falls under the subfield of computational complexity (cs.CC) and social networks (cs.SI).
